tle><link>/authors/n.-akkuratova/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/n.-akkuratova/</guid><description/></item><item><title>P. Ernfors</title><link>/authors/p.-ernfors/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/p.-ernfors/</guid><description/></item><item><title>R. Soldatov</title><link>/authors/r.-soldatov/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/r.-soldatov/</guid><description/></item><item><title>V. Dyachuk</title><link>/authors/v.-dyachuk/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/v.-dyachuk/</guid><description/></item><item><title>W. Yu Hsiao</title><link>/authors/w.-yu-hsiao/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/w.-yu-hsiao/</guid><description/></item><item><title>X. Qian</title><link>/authors/x.-qian/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/x.-qian/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Y. Yang</title><link>/authors/y.-yang/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/y.-yang/</guid><description/></item><item><title/><link>/authors/admin/</link><pubDate>Tue, 05 Feb 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/admin/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;We are known for running projects that tackle different aspects of organismal biology. We look at a range of live systems from a mechanistic point of view, trying to reverse engineer different aspects of multicellular life. Tracing the incremental advancements in development of multicellular organisms from a single cell perspective allows better understanding of the complexity of the entire organism or organ system in a final phase. That is why our main strength is developmental biology. The knowledge gained from developmental biology research is widely applied in regenerative medicine. Thus, we hope to improve human health via discovering new fundamental ideas about how development, stem cells, and regeneration work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our laboratory advances a broad spectrum of projects related to developmental biology, stem cells, EvoDevo and regenerative medicine. The methodology includes classical developmental biology approaches blended with single cell transcriptomics, 2D sequencing and 3D-reconstructions of tissues and organs based on optical or X-ray methods (micro-CT, synchrotron).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The neural crest stem cells is our primary model system, where we address general principles of cell fate choice, transcriptional and epigenetic control of a lineage progression, morphogenesis, and tissue shaping.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>A. Furlan</title><link>/authors/a.-furlan/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/a.-furlan/</guid><description/></item><item><title>D. Kamenev</title><link>/authors/d.-kamenev/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/d.-kamenev/</guid><description/></item><item><title>D. Usoskin</title><link>/authors/d.-usoskin/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/d.-usoskin/</guid><description/></item><item><title>F. Lallemend</title><link>/authors/f.-lallemend/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/f.-lallemend/</guid><description/></item><item><title>F. Memic</title><link>/authors/f.-memic/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/f.-memic/</guid><description/></item><item><title>H. Abdo</title><link>/authors/h.-abdo/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/h.-abdo/</guid><description/></item><item><title>K. Sunadome</title><link>/authors/k.-sunadome/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/k.-sunadome/</guid><description/></item><item><title>L. Calvo-Enrique</title><link>/authors/l.-calvo-enrique/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/l.-calvo-enrique/</guid><description/></item><item><title>P. Topilko</title><link>/authors/p.-topilko/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/p.-topilko/</guid><description/></item><item><title>S. Hadjab</title><link>/authors/s.-hadjab/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/authors/s.-hadjab/</guid><description/></item><item><title>U. Marklund</title><link>/authors/u.-marklund/</